’Femi Asu The Petroleum Technology Association of Nigeria says it has partnered the Nigerian Content Development and Monitoring Board to donate ambulances, Personal Protective Equipment and other medical facilities to Bayelsa, Delta and Rivers states to curb the spread of COVID-19. The Chairman of the association, Mr Nik Odinuwe, who disclosed this in Port Harcourt, said the donation was part of its corporate social responsibility initiatives, according to a statement. He said the association was aware of the immense strain the COVID-19 pandemic had placed on the healthcare system in Nigeria. He said with the PETAN’s donation, he hoped that the fight against the virus would be won in the three states and the entire country. Odinuwe thanked the healthcare personnel for their selflessness in the fight against the virus, and urged members of the public to stay in their homes, wash their hands regularly and comply with the stipulated social distancing gap. The Publicity Secretary, PETAN, Dr Lucky Akhiwu, said the whole country had been working tirelessly to slow down the spread of virus and that the association would be proud to help on a continuous basis. Copyright PUNCH.
